<br>
The 4 hour snooze was 28+ hours prior to this spawn that &quot;so and so&quot; ganked early this morning. <br>
<br>
Yes there was a contest between two clerics.  Cleric #2 arrived right after Cleric #1 (who had the RF spawn).  He told her taking a nap was ok and I'll hold your spot as long as you're back before he spawns (which she was).  Cleric #3 came in during that nap and didn't respect this claim.<br>
<br>
The Merchant spawned for Cleric #1.  The, 24 hours later, Cleric #2 and Cleric #3 are still there, vying for who's right.  During that time there was GM intervention, and those two clerics, along with two new ones who showed were forced to random for the first 4 spots.  It is THIS spawn that was ganked.<br>
<br>
ALL clerics who were there awaiting this latest RF merchant spawn KNEW the first four spawns were already assigned by the GM with that forced roll.  The cleric who ganked it knew this quite well as she was grouped with one of the two who were still contesting the #1 spot.<br>
<br>
The cleric who ganked the spawn <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  was</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> in the wrong and has done her guild tag a huge injustice.  As before, I'm keeping this clean of names/tags, <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>but I did have logs on in case any officer associated with this cleric wishes me to email them to him/her</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->.  The logs will show she was &quot;there&quot; whether casting spells or speaking during much of the conversations that took place in say prior to us taking the conversation to a chat channel so the original camp holder (cleric #1) could join in.<br>
<br>
The logs, however, will not show her speaking on the topic in say.  If any who were grouped with her had logs on, please post here.<br>
<br>
I received my epic on Friday morning but was there to show support for those camping this mob; to hope it didn't turn into bloodbath or worse.  I was there for approximately 4 hours (3 and a half hours before the Merchant popped and half an hour+ afterwards) so have a good amount of conversation recorded.<br>
